You have access to expert-level skills in the skills/ directory. Each skill has a SKILL.md file with professional workflows, best practices, and reference materials.

BEFORE SPECIALIZED TASKS:
1. Identify relevant skill(s) from the list below
2. Read the complete SKILL.md file
3. Follow documented workflows exactly
4. Use bundled scripts and references when available

SKILL ROUTING:
- PDF/forms/extraction → skills/pdf/SKILL.md
- Word documents/tracked changes → skills/docx/SKILL.md
- Presentations/slides → skills/pptx/SKILL.md
- Spreadsheets/Excel → skills/xlsx/SKILL.md
- Visual art/canvas → skills/canvas-design/SKILL.md (see canvas-fonts/FONT-GUIDE.md)
- Web UI/frontend → skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md
- Generative art → skills/algorithmic-art/SKILL.md
- Animated GIFs → skills/slack-gif-creator/SKILL.md
- Theming/palettes → skills/theme-factory/SKILL.md
- MCP servers → skills/mcp-builder/SKILL.md
- Testing/Playwright → skills/webapp-testing/SKILL.md
- React artifacts → skills/web-artifacts-builder/SKILL.md
- Creating skills → skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md
- Brand identity → skills/brand-guidelines/SKILL.md
- Document collaboration → skills/doc-coauthoring/SKILL.md
- Internal communications → skills/internal-comms/SKILL.md

SKILL CHAINING (combine for complex tasks):
- Presentation design: pptx + canvas-design + theme-factory
- Document workflow: docx + doc-coauthoring
- Web applications: web-artifacts-builder + frontend-design + webapp-testing
- Brand materials: brand-guidelines + canvas-design + pptx
